node.text:
🐐 The undisputed sport climbing GOAT
🧗‍♀️ The most successful female climber in history
🥇 Olympic champion Janja Garnbret

She's targeting Paris success in a sport growing in popularity after its Olympic debut.
"There is so much diversity and there are no limits."

@janja_garnbret I @sloveniaolympicteam

node.title: What makes sport climbing such a cool sport?

node.text: Just a few hours before the @paralympics Closing Ceremony we catch up with @birgitskarstein - a para-athlete from Norway 🇳🇴 . She competed at Sochi, Rio, PyeongChang, and now at the Tokyo 2020 Paralympic Games, where she won a gold medal. Birgit tells us why the Paralympics are so important and how she is spending her time after the Games.

node.title: Chat with Paralympic champion Birgit Skarstein

node.text:
All good things must come to an end. ❤️⁠
⁠
@gelyamelnikova reflects on winning gold at #Tokyo2020, while @morgihurd and Chen Yile look back on their @gymnastics journeys and what comes next.⁠
⁠
The #AllAround finale is now streaming.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by The Olympic Games on September 15, 2021 tagging @jakob.schubert. May be an image of 2 people and text.

node.text:
The IFSC Climbing World Champs are kicking off in Moscow tomorrow, with plenty of Olympians on show! 🧗⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Who would you like to see be crowned champion in men's and women's speed, bouldering and lead?⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Hit the link in bio for our preview, and how to watch all the action live on olympics.com.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
@ifsclimbing
